sentences: Joseph Kiambukuta Londa was born in Gombe-Matadi on Valentine's Day of 1949, to Bernard Bakiansuni and Albertine Londa.
Kiambukuta joined Dr. Nico's group, African Fiesta Sukisa in 1969.
Two years later, in 1971, he leaves to form his band Orchestre Continental with other young musicians including Wuta Mayi and Bopol Mansiamina.
Kiambukuta joined TPOK Jazz  in 1973.
Josky eventually left the group, along with Ntesa Dalienst in 1985.
Kiambukuta returned to TPOK Jazz in 1987.
After the death of Franco in 1989, TPOK Jazz continued to play for four years.
However, in 1994, conflicts forced the band to split up.
Kiambukuta is reported to have retired from music circa 2009.
He died in a Kinshasa hospital on 7 March 2021 at the age of 72.
